## Results

The Automobile Dataset was successfully preprocessed and analyzed using Python, Pandas, and Scikit-Learn. Data cleaning techniques were applied to handle missing values and prepare the dataset for machine learning. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) was performed to understand the distribution of automobile prices and the relationships between different features.

Two regression algorithms, Linear Regression and Random Forest Regressor, were implemented and evaluated. The Random Forest Regressor demonstrated superior predictive performance and was selected as the final model for car price prediction.

The trained model was able to estimate vehicle prices based on automobile characteristics such as engine size, horsepower, fuel type, body style, and other relevant features. A sample prediction generated by the model produced an estimated automobile price of approximately **14,860.26**.

Visualization techniques including price distribution plots, correlation heatmaps, and actual versus predicted price graphs were used to assess model performance and gain insights into the dataset. The results indicate that machine learning can effectively predict automobile prices and provide valuable support for buyers and sellers in making informed decisions.

## Conclusion

This project successfully developed a machine learning-based car price prediction system using the Automobile Dataset. The process involved data collection, preprocessing, exploratory data analysis, feature encoding, model training, and performance evaluation.

Among the tested models, the Random Forest Regressor provided the most reliable predictions and demonstrated strong capability in capturing complex relationships within the dataset. The model can be used to estimate the market value of vehicles based on their specifications and historical data.

The project highlights the practical application of machine learning in the automotive industry and demonstrates how predictive analytics can support pricing decisions. Future improvements may include the use of larger datasets, advanced feature engineering techniques, and more sophisticated machine learning algorithms to further enhance prediction accuracy.
